name: Biology
subject: Science
description: Study of living organisms' patterns, processes, relationships (structures, genetics, evolution, ecosystems). Includes lab investigations.

name: Biology (Advanced)
subject: Science
description: Advanced study using critical thinking/problem solving to explore biological concepts. Includes lab investigations.

name: Biology (TAG Advanced)
subject: Science
description: Advanced study for TAG students using critical thinking/problem solving to explore biological concepts. Includes lab investigations.

name: Biology, Applied
subject: Science
description: Focuses on patterns, processes, relationships of living organisms for applied students. Includes lab investigations. ARD Committee placement.

name: Functional Science I, Biology
subject: Science
description: Functional science concepts focusing on Biology. ARD Committee placement.

name: Integrated Physics & Chemistry (IPC)
subject: Science
description: Investigates force, motion, energy, and matter using physics and chemistry concepts. Includes lab investigations.

name: IPC (Integrated Physics and Chemistry), Applied
subject: Science
description: Investigates force, motion, energy, and matter using physics/chemistry concepts for applied students. Includes lab investigations. ARD Committee placement.

name: Functional Science II, IPC
subject: Science
description: Functional science concepts focusing on Integrated Physics and Chemistry. ARD Committee placement.

name: Chemistry
subject: Science
description: Study of matter, Periodic Table, atomic theory, bonding, stoichiometry, gas laws, solutions, acid-base, thermochemistry, nuclear chemistry. Includes lab investigations.

name: Chemistry (Advanced)
subject: Science
description: Advanced study focusing on depth of knowledge in chemistry concepts needed for AP. Includes lab investigations.

name: Chemistry (TAG Advanced)
subject: Science
description: Advanced study for TAG students focusing on depth of knowledge in chemistry concepts needed for AP. Includes lab investigations.

name: Chemistry, Applied
subject: Science
description: Study of chemistry concepts for applied students. Includes lab investigations. ARD Committee placement.

name: Chemistry (OnRamps College Chemistry)
subject: Science
description: OnRamps dual enrollment course covering College Chemistry Principles 1 + Lab. Potential UT credit.

name: Functional Science III Chemistry
subject: Science
description: Functional science concepts focusing on Chemistry. ARD Committee placement.

name: Physics
subject: Science
description: Study of motion, energy, momentum, forces, waves, electricity, magnetism using conceptual knowledge and experimental design. Includes lab investigations.

name: Physics 1 AP
subject: Science
description: AP Level: Equivalent to first-semester college algebra-based physics. Covers Newtonian mechanics, energy, waves, sound, circuits. Includes lab investigations.

name: Physics I (TAG AP)
subject: Science
description: AP Level for TAG students: Equivalent to first-semester college algebra-based physics. Covers Newtonian mechanics, energy, waves, sound, circuits. Includes lab investigations.

name: Physics I (OnRamps General Physics I)
subject: Science
description: OnRamps dual enrollment course covering General Physics I (Mechanics, Heat, Sound) + Lab. Potential UT credit.

name: Biology AP
subject: Science
description: College-level course developing advanced inquiry/reasoning skills across key biological concepts (Evolution, Cellular Processes, Genetics, Interactions). Includes lab investigations.

name: Biology (TAG AP)
subject: Science
description: College-level course for TAG students developing advanced inquiry/reasoning skills across key biological concepts. Includes lab investigations.

name: Biology (OnRamps Biology I + Lab)
subject: Science
description: OnRamps dual enrollment course potentially earning UT credit for Biology I + Lab.

name: Chemistry AP
subject: Science
description: College freshman-level theoretical chemistry course. Lab experiments emphasize data analysis and reports.

name: Chemistry (TAG AP)
subject: Science
description: College freshman-level theoretical chemistry course for TAG students. Lab experiments emphasize data analysis and reports.

name: Physics 2 AP
subject: Science
description: AP Level: Equivalent to second-semester college algebra-based physics. Covers fluid mechanics, thermodynamics, E&M, optics, atomic/nuclear physics. Includes lab investigations.

name: Physics II (TAG AP)
subject: Science
description: AP Level for TAG students: Equivalent to second-semester college algebra-based physics. Includes lab investigations.

name: Physics C: Electricity & Magnetism AP
subject: Science
description: AP Level: College calculus-based physics course covering electricity and magnetism. Part of a 2-credit block with Mechanics.

name: Physics C: Electricity & Magnetism (TAG AP)
subject: Science
description: AP Level for TAG students: College calculus-based physics course covering E&M. Part of a 2-credit block.

name: Physics C: Mechanics AP
subject: Science
description: AP Level: College calculus-based physics course covering mechanics. Part of a 2-credit block with E&M.

name: Physics C: Mechanics (TAG AP)
subject: Science
description: AP Level for TAG students: College calculus-based physics course covering mechanics. Part of a 2-credit block.

name: Environmental Science AP
subject: Science
description: AP Level: College-level, lab-oriented course on interdependence of Earth’s systems, human interactions, environmental effects.

name: Environmental Science (TAG AP)
subject: Science
description: AP Level for TAG students: College-level, lab-oriented course on Earth’s systems, human interactions, environmental effects.

name: Anatomy and Physiology
subject: Science
description: Study of human body systems structures, functions, interactions through integration of biology, chemistry, physics. Dissection included. Satisfies science credit.

name: Aquatic Science
subject: Science
description: Study of interactions of biotic/abiotic components in aquatic environments, including natural/human impacts. Includes lab investigations.

name: Aquatic Science, Applied
subject: Science
description: Study of interactions in aquatic environments for applied students. Includes lab investigations. ARD Committee placement.

name: Astronomy
subject: Science
description: Focuses on patterns, processes, relationships among astronomical objects in our universe. Includes lab investigations.

name: Earth Systems (OnRamps Earth, Wind, and Fire)
subject: Science
description: OnRamps dual enrollment course potentially earning UT credit for Introduction to Geoscience.

name: Environmental Systems
subject: Science
description: Study of ecosystems, biomes, resource interrelationships, energy flow, carrying capacity, population changes, natural/human impacts. Includes lab investigations.

name: Environmental Systems, Applied
subject: Science
description: Study of Environmental Systems concepts for applied students. Includes lab investigations. ARD Committee placement.

name: Functional Science IV, Environmental Systems
subject: Science
description: Functional science concepts focusing on Environmental Systems. ARD Committee placement.

name: Advanced Animal Science
subject: Science
description: Examines interrelatedness of human, scientific, tech dimensions of livestock production via field/lab experiences. Satisfies science credit.

name: Forensic Science
subject: Science
description: Structured scientific approach to crime investigation (assault, abuse, death, homicide, criminal behavior psychology). Learns terminology, procedures. Satisfies science credit.

name: Medical Microbiology
subject: Science
description: Explores microbial world: pathogenic/non-pathogenic microorganisms, lab procedures, identification, drug resistance, emerging diseases. Satisfies science credit.

name: Introduction to Engineering Design (IED-PLTW)
subject: CTE/Elective
description: Study engineering design process, create designs using 3D CAD. Sketching, dimensioning, reverse engineering. PLTW Curriculum.

name: Principles of Engineering (Engineering Science) (POE-PLTW)
subject: Science
description: Broad survey of engineering fields/careers. Develop problem-solving skills, explore systems/processes. Satisfies science credit. PLTW Curriculum.

name: Scientific Research and Design
subject: Science
description: Review scientific literature, design a research project, plan/present final products to scientific community reps. Satisfies science credit.

name: Livestock and Poultry Production
subject: CTE/Elective
description: Acquire knowledge/skills related to animal systems, workplace, careers, industry expectations.

name: Veterinary Medical Applications
subject: CTE/Elective
description: Academic/technical skills for animal systems/workplace. Veterinary practices for large/small animals. Elanco cert available.

name: Equine Science
subject: CTE/Elective
description: Enhance knowledge/skills related to animal systems (equine focus), careers, industry expectations.

name: Small Animal Management
subject: CTE/Elective
description: Enhance knowledge/skills for animal systems (small mammals, amphibians, reptiles, avian, dogs, cats), careers, industry expectations.

name: Principles of Agriculture, Food, and Natural Resources
subject: CTE/Elective
description: Enhance understanding of agriculture industry: plant/animal systems, food production, mechanical systems, entrepreneurship, leadership, environmental sciences.
